    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I hear you, but \"misguided\" is a pretty strong word to use for people who are just worried about economic competitiveness and national security. Isn't it possible that the \"existential risk\" is actually just a speculative theory used to justify control? Why should we treat it as a settled fact over the very real, tangible economic impacts?",
